{
  "slug": "oscars-2019-instant-reactions-to-green-book-and-the-two-warr",
  "title": "Oscars 2019: Instant Reactions to ‘Green Book’ and the Two Warring Academies | The Oscars Show (Ep. 131)",
  "show": "The Big Picture",
  "network": "The Ringer",
  "hosts": [
    "Sean Fennessey",
    "Amanda Dobbins"
  ],
  "published": "2019-02-25",
  "runtimeMin": 76,
  "format": "Sean Fennessey and Amanda Dobbins react, minutes after the 91st Academy Awards, to Green Book's Best Picture win and a ceremony split between an old academy and a new one, then walk all 24 categories.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The two academies",
      "note": "the contenders, the telecast, and what Green Book means",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Green Book",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Best Picture, Original Screenplay, and Mahershala Ali's Supporting Actor: the hosts read the sweep as the old academy digging in against the backlash over the Vallelonga tweets and the Don Shirley family's objections. Sean predicts that in five years people will ask how it won; the winners never thanked Shirley on stage."
        },
        {
          "title": "Roma",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "The Netflix favorite going in, tied with The Favourite for most nominations. Won Director, Cinematography, and Foreign Language for Alfonso Cuarón but lost Best Picture: the hosts frame it as Hollywood telling Netflix 'not yet.' Amanda reclaims it as a masterpiece; Sean argues Cuarón's real best films are Y Tu Mamá También and Children of Men."
        },
        {
          "title": "Bohemian Rhapsody",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Four wins including Rami Malek's Best Actor, plus Editing and both Sound categories the hosts thought belonged to First Man and A Star Is Born. Queen bled into the commercials and the Adam Lambert opening; Sean compares Malek's win to Adrien Brody for The Pianist and worries about the same career curse."
        },
        {
          "title": "BlacKkKlansman",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Spike Lee's first competitive Oscar, for Adapted Screenplay: his acceptance partly bleeped, read off paper, handed over by Sam Jackson. It felt genuine even though the hosts don't rank it near his best; they wonder whether an overdue-Scorsese-style Best Director push follows."
        },
        {
          "title": "Black Panther",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Three wins: Hannah Beachler's Production Design and Ruth Carter's Costume Design (first Black winners in those categories in 35-plus years) plus Ludwig Göransson's Score. For about five minutes the hosts thought a seven-win sweep was happening before remembering it got no acting nods and Coogler wasn't nominated for Director."
        },
        {
          "title": "A Star Is Born",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "The 'great first hour, then it dies' comparison for the whole telecast, and the source of the night's most excruciating segment: Cooper and Gaga performing 'Shallow' as themselves rather than as Jackson and Ally. Won only Original Song, and Cooper, who did nine jobs on the film, wasn't allowed on stage for it."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Favourite",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Went 1-for-10, the lone win being Olivia Colman's shock Best Actress, the most fun and only true upset of the night. The hosts feel awful for seven-time nominee Glenn Close of The Wife, who they call the inverted Sally Field."
        },
        {
          "title": "Vice",
          "year": 2018,
          "note": "Won only Makeup and Hairstyling (Greg Cannom), introduced first by Tom Morello. The hosts debate whether it fades fast or gets a Dick Cheney-driven second life, unlike Oliver Stone's forgotten Nixon and W."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Wife",
          "year": 2017,
          "note": "The Glenn Close vehicle the hosts made a whole episode about; nobody in the academy seems to have watched it, and she lost again."
        }
      ]
    },
